                <h1>Discover the Publisher of "The Yellow Wallpaper"</h1>
                <p>The "The Yellow Wallpaper," a short story by Charlotte Perkins Gilman, was first published in 1892. It appeared in the New England Magazine and has since become a seminal work in feminist literature. The narrative explores themes of mental health, gender roles, and the oppressive nature of societal expectations, reflecting the struggles of women during the late 19th century.</p>
